    App
    The `App` class is the main class of the JavaFX application.
    CurrentAndForecastWeatherRequest
    The `CurrentAndForecastWeatherRequest` class represents a request for current and forecast weather data.

    The `CurrentAndForecastWeatherResponse` class represents the One Call API 3.0 response.

    The `Alert` class represents the government weather alerts.

    The `Current` class represents the current weather data.

    A class to represent the precipitation volume.

    The `Daily` class represents the daily forecast for the next 8 days.
    CurrentAndForecastWeatherResponse.Daily.Temperature
    A class to represent the temperature.
    CurrentAndForecastWeatherResponse.Hourly
    The `Hourly` class represents the hourly forecast for the next 48 hours.
    CurrentAndForecastWeatherResponse.Hourly.Precipitation
    A class to represent the precipitation volume.
    CurrentAndForecastWeatherResponse.Minutely
    The `Minutely` class represents the minute forecast for the next hour.

    The `Weather` class represents the weather condition.
    CurrentWeatherRequest
    The `CurrentWeatherRequest` class represents a request for current weather data.
    CurrentWeatherResponse
    The `CurrentWeatherResponse` class represents the response for current weather data.
    GeoCodingAPICall
    The `GeoCodingAPICall` class represents a call to the OpenWeatherMap GeoCoding API.
    GeoCodingRequest
    The `GeoCodingRequest` class represents the request parameters for the OpenWeatherMap GeoCoding API call.
    GeoCodingResponse
    The `GeoCodingResponse` class represents the response for the OpenWeatherMap GeoCoding API call.
    HistoricalWeatherRequest
    The `HistoricalWeatherRequest` class represents a request to retrieve historical weather data.
    HistoricalWeatherResponse
    The `HistoricalWeatherResponse` class represents a response containing historical weather data.
    Place
    The `Place` class represents a location on Earth.
    RunMain
    The `RunMain` class is the entry point for the application.
    StartScreenController
    The `StartScreenController` class is the controller for the start screen of the weather application.
    WeatherAPICall
    The WeatherAPICall class contains methods to interact with the OpenWeatherMap API and retrieve various weather-related data such as current weather, historical weather, forecast, moon phase information, and weather-related images.
    WeatherAppLocalFile
    The WeatherAppLocalFile class represents the local configuration file for the Weather App.
    WeatherFileHandler
    The `WeatherFileHandler` class provides methods to read from and write to a local file containing user preference data.
    WeatherScreenController
    Controller class responsible for managing the Weather Screen GUI functionality.
